      "created": "2014-05-21T12:11:22.254+0000",
      "description": "The {{AmIpFilter}} doesn't like REST APIs, as all operations are redirected to the proxy as a 302. Even if the proxy did relay all verbs, the filter would need to return a 307 and hope the client was enable to re-issue the verb.\n\nThe alternative is to have a dedicated part of the webapp to be unproxied, which we did with a custom filter to not relay \"/ws/*\", or even allow apps to register a rest endpoint directly, either in the AppReport data, or via the YARN-913 registry",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/resolution/2",
        "id": "2",
        "description": "The problem described is an issue which will never be fixed.",
        "name": "Won't Fix"
      },
